AGI -&nbsp;Aiea fears that Israel targets Iranian nuclear plants. Tehran closed his nuclear facilities on Sunday for "security considerations", says the agency's general manager, Rafael Grossi. On Monday, as they reopen, he kept the inspectors away "until we have proof that the situation is completely calm" reported the Times of Israel citing Reuters. "We'll get back tomorrow," Grossi told reporters in New York.
&nbsp;
"This has had no impact on our inspection activity." When asked about the possibility of an Israeli attack on Iranian nuclear plants, Grossi replied that "there is always concern for this possibility" and urged the "maximum moderation". &nbsp;
Iran temporarily closed its nuclear installations for "security reasons" following the massive attack launched against Israel last Saturday night. Rafael Grossi, head of the International Atomic Energy Agency (Aiea) said that inspectors will not resume work "until we have seen that the situation is completely calm".

