AGI - The President of the United States, Joe Biden, and the first lady, Jill Biden, published their income statement 2023, continuing a tradition of transparency temporarily interrupted under the mandate of their predecessor Donald Trump.
&nbsp;
The Biden earned $619,976 in 2023, most of which came from the President's $400,000 salary > and Jill Biden's $85,985 fee for his work as a professor at a university in nearby Virginia.
&nbsp;
The figure is more than $579.514 earned by the couple in 2022 and 610.702 in 2021.&nbsp;Trump refused both as a candidate and once in charge of publishing his income statement. When several years of his reports were finally made public as a result of a legal battle taken by the Democrats in Congress, it was discovered that there were years when Trump did not pay nearly any income tax due to company losses. Trump continued to keep his income statements secret while preparing to campaign for the November presidential elections.

